verbose_text: The Brillouin function analysis could very nicely explain the magnetization data of both insulating SrTi 0.98 Mn 0.02 O 2.99 and metallic SrTi 0.99 Mn 0.01 O 2.96 samples, as shown in XREF_FIG, and the extracted paramagnetic Mn dopings from the fits to the experimental data were found to be consistent with corresponding nominal Mn doping levels, as discussed in the earlier section.
